%text Let there be two events - $A$ and $B$ If event B has already happened, then event $A$ has also either happened or not happened. There is no third possiblility Mathematically, this rather obvious fact is expressed as follows \[\qquad P\left( A\,\vert\,B \right) + P\left( A'\,\vert\, B\right) = 1\]
% \begin{align} \begin{tabular}{Nc}
\hline \text{Notation} & \text{Probability of $\ldots$} \\ \hline P \left(A\vert B \right) & \text{$A$ happening given $B$} \\ \hline P \left(A'\vert B \right) & \text{$A$ not happening given $B$} \\ \hline \end{tabular} \end{align} %text %
